From 8205a0bcd4c47f5f68cca8261c15f20c483e1a74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: test <test@example.invalid>
Date: Sun, 31 May 2026 20:24:50 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] hibyr1: add platform PCM hooks and HiBy weak overrides

Introduce weak symbol hooks in pcm-alsa.c to allow platforms to customize
ALSA behavior without fragmenting the shared backend with #ifdefs.

Hooks allow customization of:
- Buffer/period sizing per device type
- Start threshold for different latency profiles
- Device lifecycle management (open/close hooks)
- Poll interval calculation for custom poll threads

HiBy implementation provides overrides for Bluetooth (BlueALSA) support:
- Larger buffers for wireless latency
- Custom poll thread instead of async callbacks
- Device-specific start thresholds

This eliminates all HIBY_LINUX conditionals from pcm-alsa.c while keeping
platform logic isolated in overlay files.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

Extract the body of async_callback() into a new exported function
pcm_alsa_pump_locked() (caller holds pcm_mtx) so the HiBy poll thread in
pcm-alsa-hiby.c can drive the PCM. async_callback() now just takes the
mutex and delegates. Without this definition the HiBy build failed to
link (undefined reference to pcm_alsa_pump_locked).
